{"lemma":"طاغُوتَيْ","slug":"طاغُوتَيْ","root":"ط.غ.#","root_slug":"ط-غ-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-غ-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طاغُوت","root":"طغي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26785"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"idol, juggernaut, taghut","examples":[{"text":"لَا إِكْرَاهَ فِي ٱلدِّينِ قَد تَّبَيَّنَ ٱلرُّشْدُ مِنَ ٱلْغَيِّ فَمَن يَكْفُرْ بِٱلطَّاغُوتِ وَيُؤْمِن بِٱللَّهِ فَقَدِ ٱسْتَمْسَكَ بِٱلْعُرْوَةِ الْوُثْقَى لَا ٱنْفِصَامَ لَهَا وَٱللَّهُ سَمِيعٌ عَلِيمٌ","english":"There shall be no compulsion in the religion. The right course has become clear from the wrong. So whoever disbelieves in false idols and believes in God has grasped the most trustworthy handhold with no break in it. And God is Hearing and Knowing."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Ordered at the root ط غ و (ṭ ḡ w) or ط غ ي (ṭ ḡ y) related to transgression and explained as a being “transgressing the law”. However it is considered a loanword:\n* from Ge'ez ጣዖት (ṭaʿot, “idol”), from Hebrew טָעוּת (ṭaʿút, “error”), from Jewish Babylonian Aramaic and Jewish Palestinian Aramaic טעותא (ṭaʿúta, “idol, false god”)\n* with Wahib Atallah from Egyptian ḏḥwtj (“Thoth”) as a personification of superstitious practices, while he sees جِبْت (jibt) used with طَاغُوت (ṭāḡūt) in hendiadys in Qurʾān 4:51 as reflecting Hijazi pronunciation of قِبْط (qibṭ, “Egyptians”)"},"ipa":["/tˤaː.ɣuːt/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26785","headword_ar":"طَاغُوتٌ","root":"Tgw and TgY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaEuwtN","text_ar":"فَلَعُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tagawotu","text_ar":"طَغَوْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) formed by transposition, though like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAhuwtN","text_ar":"لَاهُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is not so formed: (S:) it is originally of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaluwtN","text_ar":"فَعَلُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is changed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaEuwtN","text_ar":"فَلَعُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaguwtN","text_ar":"طَوَغُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and this is then altered to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAguwtN","text_ar":"طَاغُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) it is held to be altered from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawaguwt","text_ar":"طَوَغُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"rather than from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tagayuwt","text_ar":"طَغَيُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the transposition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common than that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkK","text_ar":"شَاكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (M, TA:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the measure is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEuwlN","text_ar":"فَاعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and some say that the measure is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEaluwtN","text_ar":"فَاعَلُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAgayuwtN","text_ar":"طَاغَيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAgiytu","text_ar":"طَوَاغِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAgK","text_ar":"طَوَاغٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the latter mentioned by ISd. (TA.) It signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A devil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA;) thus expl. by Abu-l- 'Áliyeh and others, and said to be on the authority of 'Omar: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is exorbitant in pride"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruptness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disbelief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedience, of the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAguwtu","text_ar":"الطَّاغُوتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the idol called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~aAt","text_ar":"اللَّات"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuz~aY","text_ar":"العُزَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or thus some expl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljibot","text_ar":"الجِبْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAguwt","text_ar":"الطَّاغُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[together, in the Kur iv. 54]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever is worshipped instead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the exclusion, of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljibotu","text_ar":"الجِبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the idols"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in general"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the idols,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who turns from the good way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the diviner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the enchanter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus expl. by 'Ikrimeh; and said to mean thus in the Kur iv. 63: and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljibotu","text_ar":"الجِبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Zj: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leader, of error:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exorbitant in pride"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruptness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disbelief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedience, of the people of the Scripture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) it is used as a sing., (S, K,) as in the Kur iv. 63; (S;) and as a pl., (S, K,) as in the Kur ii. 259; (S;) and masc. and fem., (Msb, TA,) as fem. in the Kur xxxix. 19: (TA:) or by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljibot","text_ar":"الجِبْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant Hoyeí Ibn-Akhtab; and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAguwt","text_ar":"الطَّاغُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":", Kaab Ibn-ElAshraf: (I'Ab, K:) and [the pls.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAgiytu","text_ar":"طَوَاغِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAgK","text_ar":"طَوَاغٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify [sometimes]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"idol temples:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says El-Háfidh in the preface to the “ Fet-h ” [i. e. his celebrated work entitled “ Fet-h el-Bári ”]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","M","K","Zj","Akh"]}]}}